# Backend Rules (Authoritative Enforcement)

Canonical references (read before every change):
- `server/ai-rules/architecture.md`
- `server/ai-rules/development-guidelines.md`
- `server/ai-rules/security.md`
- `server/ai-rules/decisions.md`

Conflicts resolve in favor of the above files, then this file, then task prompt.

---

## Modules

- DO keep two Maven modules only: `processor-core`, `processor-api`.
- DO keep `processor-core` free of Spring, JPA, Hibernate, SQL, HTTP.
- DO NOT add any `org.springframework.*`, `jakarta.persistence.*`, `org.hibernate.*`, `javax.sql.*` import in `processor-core`.
- DO NOT create a new top-level module without an ADR.

## Layering

- DO place code in the correct package per `architecture.md §7`.
- DO enforce dependency direction: Controller → ApplicationService → DomainService → RepositoryPort.
- DO NOT let inner layers import outer layers.
- DO NOT put business logic in Controllers or ApplicationServices.
- DO keep business logic exclusively in DomainService classes inside `processor-core`.

## Controllers

- DO make controllers thin: parse, validate with `@Valid`, delegate, return.
- DO return `ResponseEntity<T>` or typed response DTOs with appropriate status codes.
- DO NOT inject any `Repository*` (port or JPA) into controllers.
- DO NOT inject `DomainService` directly into controllers; go through `ApplicationService`.
- DO NOT accept or return JPA entities in controller signatures.
- DO NOT call `SecurityContextHolder` in controllers; resolve principal in the application layer.
- DO NOT throw raw `RuntimeException`; throw typed domain/api exceptions.

## Application Services

- DO use `@Service` + `@Transactional` here (only here for write flows).
- DO map DTO → Domain on the way in, Domain → DTO on the way out.
- DO orchestrate multiple DomainServices if a use case requires it.
- DO enforce ownership / authorization before delegating.
- DO NOT contain business rules.
- DO NOT bypass DomainService and talk to ports directly for decisions (queries are OK).

## Domain Services (core)

- DO contain all business rules, invariants, and validation logic.
- DO depend only on `RepositoryPort` interfaces and domain types.
- DO NOT depend on Spring (`@Service`, `@Autowired`, etc.), JPA, SQL, or HTTP.
- DO NOT import from `processor-api`.
- DO NOT use JPA entities or DTOs.

## Repositories

- DO define `RepositoryPort` interfaces in `processor-core/port/repository/` using domain types.
- DO implement them as `RepositoryAdapter` classes in `processor-api/persistence/adapter/`.
- DO encapsulate Spring Data JPA interfaces inside the adapter package — never inject them outside.
- DO map Entity ↔ Domain inside the adapter.
- DO NOT return JPA entities from a port method.
- DO NOT accept JPA entities as port method arguments.

## Domain vs Entity

- DO keep domain models in `core/domain/model/`.
- DO keep JPA entities in `api/persistence/entity/`, suffixed `Entity`.
- DO NOT annotate domain models with JPA annotations.
- DO NOT reuse a JPA entity as a domain model (or vice-versa).

## Dependency Injection

- DO use constructor injection with `final` fields.
- DO prefer Lombok `@RequiredArgsConstructor` on Spring beans.
- DO NOT use `@Autowired` on fields or setters.
- DO NOT use field-level `@Inject`.

## Transactions

- DO place `@Transactional` only on ApplicationService methods.
- DO use `@Transactional(readOnly = true)` for read flows.
- DO NOT annotate DomainService, Controller, or RepositoryAdapter methods with `@Transactional`.

## Security

- DO keep `SecurityFilterChain` deny-by-default; explicitly `permitAll()` only the allow-list in `security.md §6`.
- DO validate JWT signature, `iss`, `aud`, `exp` in every protected request.
- DO use `BCryptPasswordEncoder` (strength 12) for passwords.
- DO mask card numbers in logs to last 4 digits.
- DO NOT log passwords, tokens, or full card numbers.
- DO NOT store secrets in YAML or properties files.
- DO NOT accept a user id from the request body to decide ownership — use the authenticated principal.

## Validation

- DO validate request DTOs with `@Valid` + Jakarta constraints.
- DO re-validate domain invariants inside DomainService (defense in depth).
- DO set `spring.jackson.deserialization.fail-on-unknown-properties=true`.
- DO NOT rely solely on DTO validation for business invariants.

## Error Handling

- DO route all exceptions through one `@RestControllerAdvice GlobalExceptionHandler`.
- DO return a uniform `ApiError` body (`code`, `message`, `details`, `traceId`).
- DO NOT leak stack traces or framework messages to clients.
- DO NOT `catch (Exception e)` without re-throwing or transforming with cause.

## Money

- DO use `BigDecimal` for all monetary values, constructed from `String`.
- DO specify scale and rounding on division (default scale 2, `HALF_EVEN`).
- DO compare with `compareTo`.
- DO NOT use `double` or `float` for money anywhere.
- DO NOT construct `BigDecimal` from `double` literals.

## API Conventions

- DO version endpoints under `/api/v1/...`.
- DO use plural, kebab-case resource names.
- DO paginate list endpoints (`page`, `size`, `sort` allowlist).
- DO NOT invent non-standard status codes.
- DO NOT use `@RequestMapping` without an HTTP method specialization.

## Persistence

- DO manage schema with Flyway migrations.
- DO use `NUMERIC(19, 4)` for money columns.
- DO NOT edit a migration after it has been deployed; add a new one.
- DO NOT use `cascade = ALL` on `@ManyToOne`.

## Logging

- DO use `@Slf4j` / SLF4J with parameterized messages.
- DO include a request/trace id via MDC.
- DO NOT use `System.out`, `System.err`, or `printStackTrace`.
- DO NOT concatenate strings in log calls.

## Testing

- DO keep `processor-core` tests free of Spring context.
- DO use `@WebMvcTest`, `@DataJpaTest`, or Testcontainers slice tests in `processor-api`.
- DO NOT use `Thread.sleep` in tests.

## Anti-Patterns (Immediate Reject)

- Inject `JpaRepository` / Spring Data repository into Controller or DomainService.
- Return a JPA Entity from a controller.
- Place `@Transactional` on a controller method.
- Any Spring import inside `processor-core`.
- `new BigDecimal(0.1)`.
- `String sql = "SELECT ..."` assembled from request input.
- Field `@Autowired` on any bean.
- Silencing exceptions with `catch (Exception ignored) {}`.
- `@CrossOrigin("*")` in production configuration.
- Custom crypto / hash rolling.

---

When in doubt: prefer the rule in `ai-rules/*.md`. Ask before deviating.
